&lt;p&gt;Are you interested in Public Health and making a difference to children, young people and their families?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If yes, the North Yorkshire West Emotional Resilience Team are recruiting an enthusiastic Band 5 Nurse to join the team on a fixed term contract. This is a varied job working in a skill mix team with the children, young people and their families .The team is led by a SCPHN (School Nurse) and you will be expected to work independently with delegated pieces of work. Your work will be in various places including schools, community settings and family homes. Creativity and innovation are encouraged to plan and deliver public health interventions. Effective communication skills are required as working with our partners is essential to delivering an excellent service coupled with listening to our clients and promoting engagement. At HDFT our values of being respectful, passionate and responsible are at the heart of our practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware this advert is for 2 positions, 1 x 37.5 hours per week and 1 x 22.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
